HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 872
By Salinas
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Dorothy McCorkle
Wellford of Cordova.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Dorothy McCorkle Wellford; and
WHEREAS, Dorothy Wellford was an exemplary volunteer whose service to First
Presbyterian Church in Memphis and its soup kitchen, Meals on Wheels, and the Memphis
community reflected a lifelong commitment to helping others; and
WHEREAS, through her abiding commitment to serving her church, her community, and
this State, Mrs. Wellford gave freely of her time and talents in ways that reflected her deep
sense of public service; and
WHEREAS, Dorothy Wellford served First Presbyterian Church in Memphis as a
substitute organist, elder, choir member, and member of the Women of the Church; she also
served as moderator for the Presbytery-wide Women of the Church, for which she was awarded
an honorary lifetime membership; and
WHEREAS, demonstrating great dedication, Mrs. Wellford provided flowers from her
own gardens for worship services at First Presbyterian Church, growing, arranging, and placing
floral arrangements each Sunday for approximately forty years; and
WHEREAS, Dorothy Wellford was an avid tennis player who competed alongside her
husband, Dabney Wellford, to whom she was married for sixty-three years prior to his passing in
2018; together, they competed in numerous United States Tennis Association leagues; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Wellford coached women's tennis for many years and participated in
the National Senior Olympics in mixed doubles tennis with her husband, and in women's
doubles, earning a silver medal in the 80–85 age category with her women's partner; and
