WHEREAS, Dorothy Wellford and her husband led efforts for many years to collect and
transport leftover baked goods from local businesses to the First Presbyterian Church Soup
Kitchen and regularly provided nutritious, home-delivered meals and safety checks through
Meals on Wheels and the Memphis Inter-Faith Association; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Wellford is survived by her children, Dabney (Carolyn) Wellford, Jr.,
Brandon (Charissa) Wellford, and Evelyn (Jon) Walker; grandchildren, Diana (Jason)Turner,
Nicole Wellford, Robert Wellford, Anne (Daniel) Mitchell, and Mac Walker; great-grandson,
Brisbane Turner; and nine nieces and nephews; and
WHEREAS, Dorothy Wellford leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in
public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all her chosen
endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
remember the bountiful life of this exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Dorothy McCorkle Wellford, reflecting fondly upon
her impeccable character and her stalwart commitment to living the examined life with courage
and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mrs. Wellford.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
